    <abstract>
      <t>
        This document describes a new mode operation for IS-IS. In addition
        to the existing LAN and point-to-point mode of operation, a point-to-multipoint
        mode is defined. This mode is useful for operation both on networks with more than
        two routers where multicast is expensive in comparison to unicast and on
        networks where the common methodology of creating a LAN pseudonode cannot adequately
        reflect metrics.
      </t>
    </abstract>
